    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-09">December 9 (?),
                            1943</date>.]<note n="1" xml:id="d512fn1">Sent by the United States
                            Military Attaché London, at 9:48 a.m. on December 9, 1943. The time of
                            origination in Cairo does not appear on the source text.</note>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>509. Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                    >Roosevelt</persName>. Most secret and personal.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I gave the paper in my immediately following to <persName corresp="#p_II1"
                            >Inönü</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d512fn2">Annex A to the minutes of
                            the <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>-<persName
                                corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName> meeting of December 7, 1943, <hi
                                rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_755">p. 755</ref>.</note>
                        They have asked for 4 days in which to consult their Parliament but
                        meanwhile will allow build up to begin and 250 specialists are starting
                        forthwith. On the whole I am hopeful. <persName corresp="#p_VAY1"
                            >Vyshinsky</persName> liked the layout.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>… I am tidying up with the King of Greece and expect a solution and
                        arrangement in harmony with your feelings.<note n="3" xml:id="d512fn3">See
                                <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_844">pp. 844</ref>,
                                <ref target="#pg_850">850</ref>.</note> Every good wish to you and
                            <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Harry</persName>.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
